Profile
Motivated and detail-oriented Computer Engineering graduate with a solid foundation in object-oriented programming, database management, and software development.
Proficient in C# and Microsoft SQL Server, with practical experience developing desktop-based applications such as a Salon Management System.
Adept at designing intuitive user interfaces and managing robust backend operations.
A fast learner with strong problem-solving abilities, committed to delivering scalable software solutions and thriving in collaborative, technology-driven environments.
Projects
Face and Iris Based Attendance System
Designed and developed a desktop-based Python application for automating attendance tracking.
Utilized facial and iris recognition for biometric identification and verification.
Implemented advanced image processing and ML algorithms for accurate recognition.
Enabled real-time data capture via webcam (including phone IP camera).
Ensured secure storage of attendance records in structured formats (e.g., CSV).
Integrated detailed attendance reporting and data management features.
Demonstrated strong skills in Python, OpenCV, and biometric authentication systems.
Salon Management System
Developed a desktop-based application in C# to streamline salon operations.
Included key modules: customer management, appointment scheduling, service tracking, and billing.
Applied object-oriented programming (OOP) principles for modular and maintainable code.
Designed an intuitive GUI using Windows Forms for smooth user navigation.
Integrated MS SQL Server for backend support with data normalization, indexing, and stored procedures.
